    "lastHeartbeatText": "The user is getting an error when clicking on a topic. The error mentions ChromeDevTools running - this sounds like the browser automation is being triggered somehow when clicking topics.\n\nThis is unexpected - topics should just be search links. Let me check what's happening.\n\nThe error message mentions `RunningChromeVersion` - this suggests OpenClaw's browser is being initialized when it shouldn't be.\n\nLooking at the wiki-server.cjs code, topics should just create links like:\n`<a href=\"/?search=${encodeURIComponent(t)}\" style=\"background:...\">${t}</a>`\n\nBut when you click them, they're somehow trying to use OpenClaw browser functionality. This is likely because something in the codebase is importing or triggering OpenClaw browser functionality inappropriately.\n\nLet me investigate what's happening.",
